Container Image Creation
As user john on node1 192.168.1.107, build a container image named web_image using the container file located at http://repo.rhcsa.home/containers/Containerfile

SystemD rootless container service
	as root loginctl enable-linger john
#deploy john_web container with the following:
#map host port 8000 --> container port 80
#map the host directory /opt/user_files to container dir /opt/user_files. Files should be accessible
#build image
	podman image built -t web_image -f http://repo.rhcsa.home/containers/Containerfile
#deply container in detached and interactive mode map host port 8000 to 80 
	podman run -dit --name john_web -p 8000:80 -v /opt/user_fies:/opt/userfiles:z web_image
	podman exec -i john_web /bin/bash
	echo "test" >> test
Configure the container as a systemd service to start boot
	podman ps
	podman generate systemd --new --files --name john_web
	mkdir -p ~/.config/systed/user
	mv container-john_web.service ~/.config/systemd/user
	podman stop john_web
	podman rm john_web
	podman ps -a
	systemctl --user daemon-reload
	loginctl enable-linger
	systemctl --user enable --now container-john_web.service
	systemctl --uer status container-john_web.service
	podman ps
	
